- Talebox.dev - built an offline-first ‚Äúpersonal cloud‚Äù with collaboration and real-time data updates; Rust/Svelte/WebSocket stack.

Believe in-depth knowledge about deterministic systems (and damn good error handling üêõ) is crucial to receive expected results.

Designing pcb's (also) from ground up and getting them fabbed (again) in JLC with availble components.

projects.name: Samn
projects.description: A network of sensors AVR based, with nrf24 & cc1101 radios for 2.4GHz/915MHz control.
highlights: Designing pcb's from ground up and getting them fabbed in JLC with availble components. About 2 weeks of sleepless nights.
Testing pcb's functionality and designing the software and UI for Node / HQ (Talebox) & Svelte UI all simultaneously. About a month.
Currently still debugging tablebox's thread locking up after a very specific kind of message from rf nodes. Deployed with debugging info waitng to debug with gdb.
